&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consumer Operations, Program Manager - Stripe, LLC - New York, NY&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe, LLC. is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead or collaborate with cross-functional teams, including Product, Engineering, Legal, Compliance, Support, Operations Technology, and Vendor Management, to define operational requirements for new Link/Crypto onramp products, features, and experiments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product and Engineering teams to design and implement the infrastructure and tools needed to support operational workflows.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the interests of users in product development discussions and advocate for solutions that improve the consumer experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop customer support strategies and implement tools to enhance self-service options for users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Ensure operational processes and product features comply with applicable local laws, regulations, and consumer protection requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and analyze operational metrics, driving continuous improvements to meet key performance objectives, such as consumer satisfaction, contact rate, and service-level agreements (SLAs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Must have a Bachelor&#39;s degree or foreign equivalent in Business, Management, Economics or a related field, plus 5 years of post bachelor&#39;s progressive experience in Operations. Must also have each of the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 years experience pulling data, creating queries and analyzing large datasets using SQL.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4 years experience leading end-to-end execution of large, cross-functional projects to improve user and Support Specialist experience and operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 year of experience with designing and executing comprehensive test cases for new features, system updates, and process changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 year experience coordinating feedback loops between end users, support teams and product teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 year experience writing Product Requirement Documents (PRDs) and Business Requirement Documents (BRDs) and the ability to translate operational needs into technical requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 year experience with CRM and support platforms including Salesforce, Case Studio, and CRV, including designing and implementing automations, workflows, and routing logic to reduce manual tasks for Support agents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: $150,301 - $210,600/yr&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This salary range represents the base salary range for the role and any sales commissions /sales bonuses targets, if applicable, would be in addition to the base salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;40 hrs/week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;50% Telecommuting permitted&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Multiple Positions Available.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional benefits for this role may include: equity, company bonus or sales commissions/bonuses; 401(k) plan; medical, dental, and vision benefits; and wellness stipends.&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NY33 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;#LI-DNI&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Product&amp;nbsp; - Connect Platform&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Connect is Stripe’s platform for businesses that serve other businesses. It gives platforms the infrastructure to represent the people and companies in their ecosystem, onboard and verify them, manage their accounts, accept payments, and pay them out - without building payments, compliance, or financial-services systems themselves. This is how businesses like Shopify can help entrepreneurs run and grow their businesses. It is also the kind of infrastructure that marketplaces such as DoorDash need to coordinate money movement across large networks of restaurants, merchants, and dashers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Connect has impact across industries. &lt;a href=&quot;https://stripe.com/customers/shopify&quot;&gt;Shopify&lt;/a&gt; uses Stripe to embed financial services for merchants; &lt;a href=&quot;https://stripe.com/customers/lugg&quot;&gt;Lugg&lt;/a&gt; streamlines worker onboarding and offers instant payouts; &lt;a href=&quot;https://stripe.com/customers/doorloop&quot;&gt;DoorLoop&lt;/a&gt; reduces manual customer onboarding tasks by nearly 50% with Stripe; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://stripe.com/customers/sharetribe&quot;&gt;Sharetribe&lt;/a&gt; helps entrepreneurs launch and run marketplaces on Stripe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AI is accelerating the emergence of entirely new business models: global networks of creators and experts, AI-native marketplaces, and agent-driven products that change how people discover, buy, sell, and deliver services. These businesses are more dynamic than traditional platforms: participants may operate across borders, take on different roles, and need new ways to establish trust, access financial capabilities, and get paid.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Connect Abstractions team owns the platform primitives that make these models possible. We are building the foundational abstractions for representing participants, onboarding them safely, configuring their capabilities, and managing their lifecycle on Stripe. Our work will determine how quickly the next generation of platforms can launch, how flexibly they can evolve, and how much of Stripe they can bring to the businesses and people they serve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why this role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a chance to define a foundational product area at Stripe. You will turn a fast-changing set of user and product needs into durable platform primitives that work across products, industries, and geographies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role combines high-leverage strategy with hands-on product execution. You will work through ambiguous, consequential questions like: what should a platform be able to model? What should be simple by default but flexible when needed? How can Stripe make complex financial infrastructure feel effortless for a platform and its users?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The outcome of your work will compound. The abstractions you help create will be reused across Connect and Stripe, shaping what new products platforms can build and how quickly they can bring them to market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an entrepreneurial Product Manager to build the platform experiences behind Connect&#39;s next generation of users. You will own critical product primitives that platforms, including the fastest-growing AI companies, use to onboard, configure, and manage their users on Stripe. You will turn a clear strategic direction into products that solve hard user problems today while creating a coherent, extensible foundation for business models that are still being invented.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is for someone who enjoys the depth of platform work but is uncompromising about product craft and solving real user needs - both the ones users have today and will have in the future. The work is not building infra for its own sake; you will build capabilities that help our users launch a new marketplace, enable a global network to pay its contributors, or give a business entirely new ways for their end users to earn.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring the next generation of Connect accounts to life. Own key product areas within the account platform, translating strategy into a focused roadmap, crisp product decisions, and high-quality launches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build from use cases. Start with the real problems platforms face, such as onboarding a new seller, supporting a complex business model, or evolving a user&#39;s financial capabilities, and then work towards the primitives needed to solve them well.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make sophisticated infrastructure feel simple. Partner with engineering and design to create API and product experiences that are powerful and intuitive.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;See around corners. Develop a strong point of view on how AI will change platform economics, participant models, and financial workflows. Make focused foundational investments that unlock the next wave of demand.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Turn user signals into durable product investments. Work closely with users, Sales, Partnerships, and other Stripe teams to distinguish bespoke requests from patterns that should become scalable platform capabilities, connecting business needs, user needs, and platform evolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive high-velocity, high-craft execution and own outcomes. Lead cross-functional work from discovery through launch, and hold yourself accountable for developer experience, platform adoption, user value, and business impact, not simply features shipped.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a product builder who can move easily between a user’s hardest problem, the business opportunity behind it, and the product decisions needed to solve it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have worked on technically complex products - such as APIs, developer tools, shared platform capabilities, or core product experiences - but you do not build tech/platform for its own sake. You see strong platform design as a way to help users move faster, create better products, and unlock new business models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are opinionated, thoughtful, and execution-oriented. You can focus a team on the few decisions that matter most, create momentum in ambiguous situations, and ship products that raise the bar for both quality and impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of product management experience, with meaningful time owning platform, API, or developer-facing products end to end&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to own a product area end to end: setting strategy, driving execution, and measuring outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical instincts and comfort defining the measurement framework before you ship&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear written communication and the ability to build alignment across functions and levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in payments, fintech, or financial infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience productizing bespoke or custom solutions into broadly available platform capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of making well-judged foundational investments ahead of user demand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;GAQ327R268&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;1648&quot;&gt;While candidates in the listed location(s) are encouraged for this role, candidates in other locations will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Databricks continues to grow organically and through numerous strategic acquisitions. We’re looking to scale our M&amp;amp;A engine to handle high-volume and high-complexity deals. As the Staff Program Manager, you will oversee and lead the &quot;engine room&quot; of our People M&amp;amp;A team, transforming manual workflows, undocumented process, and numerous spreadsheets into a world-class, automated execution machine. You will bridge the gap between Corporate Development and our functional People teams to ensure every &quot;Brickster&quot; joins with a seamless, error-free experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a strategic builder who think from first principles. You don’t just follow a playbook; you engineer the platform that allows us to scale. You are someone who moves seamlessly between detailed strategy and deep-dive execution, energized by the technical complexity of M&amp;amp;A and the fast-paced velocity of our growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;2006&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-renderer-mark=&quot;true&quot;&gt;The impact you will have: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Standardize the Playbook:&lt;/strong&gt; Operationalize tribal knowledge into a documented, E2E M&amp;amp;A Playbook and Knowledge Hub to eliminate dependency on a small group of experts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Automation:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with People Tech to design and execute the &quot;Tech Efficiency Roadmap,&quot; utilizing automation and AI into our workflows/deal phases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execution Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead the People M&amp;amp;A phases of the deal. Manage the complex orchestration of recruiting, IT onboarding, and HR operations from deal disclosure through Day 1.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Integrity:&lt;/strong&gt; Design and establish &quot;Single Source of Truth&quot; protocols and data ownership matrices to ensure 100% accuracy in employee data across all systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Partnership:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as the primary POC of the People team (TA, Benefits, PeopleOps, People Partners, Global Mobility) to ensure the People M&amp;amp;A priorities are roadmapped, tracked and implemented.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;2367&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-renderer-mark=&quot;true&quot;&gt;What we look for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of M&amp;amp;A experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Speed matters, you don&#39;t wait for a playbook; you plan fast, drive alignment and execute&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re a problem solver, with multiple successful M&amp;amp;A project and process transformations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep technical knowledge of People processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing, scaling, transforming People workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategy &amp;amp; planning mindset, execution/delivery, influencing executive stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
